&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong data-stringify-type=&quot;bold&quot;&gt;About StarRez&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;StarRez is the global leader in student housing software, providing innovative solutions for on and off-campus housing management, resident wellness and experience, and revenue generation. Trusted by 1,400+ clients across 25+ countries, StarRez supports more than 4 million beds annually with its user-friendly, all-in-one platform, delivering seamless experiences for students and administrators. With offices in the United States, Australia, the UK, and India, StarRez blends the robust capabilities of a global organization with the personalized care and service of a trusted partner.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(40, 114, 214);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About College Pads&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;College Pads is transforming the way students navigate the transition from on-campus to off-campus life. Our platform enables universities to support their students by streamlining the process of finding and securing off-campus housing. By working closely with higher education institutions, we offer a trusted tool for students to connect with property managers and rental listings, helping to foster a foundation for wellbeing and success. As of January 2025, College Pads is part of StarRez.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(40, 114, 214);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a results-driven Regional Account Executive to join our dynamic sales team. In this role, you’ll build strong relationships with landlords, property managers, and real estate professionals. You will be responsible for expanding our regional presence, prospecting new clients, closing deals, and managing ongoing client relationships. As a Regional Account Executive, you will collaborate closely with marketing, client success, and customer service teams to drive strategic growth and long-term client retention.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(40, 114, 214);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Specifics&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Remote, US&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Travel:&lt;/strong&gt; 25% (The percentage of travel is an estimation, and it could vary up or down based on business needs throughout the year.)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation Structure: &lt;/strong&gt;In addition to the base salary listed below,&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;this role is eligible for a bonus/commission plan.&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; When meeting 100% of goals, the expected total annual compensation for this role is $170,000.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reporting Structure:&lt;/strong&gt; This role reports to the Sales Manager.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Application Deadline: This role will accept applications on a rolling basis until filled.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(40, 114, 214);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Own&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identifying, prospecting, and securing new partnerships with landlords and property managers within your assigned region&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Delivering tailored sales presentations, effectively communicating the benefits of our platform, and negotiating contracts to close new business&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Building and maintaining strong, long-lasting relationships with existing clients, ensuring their satisfaction and maximizing opportunities for upsell and retention&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;l

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong data-stringify-type=&quot;bold&quot;&gt;About StarRez&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;StarRez is the global leader in student housing software, providing innovative solutions for on and off-campus housing management, resident wellness and experience, and revenue generation. Trusted by 1,400+ clients across 25+ countries, StarRez supports more than 4 million beds annually with its user-friendly, all-in-one platform, delivering seamless experiences for students and administrators. With offices in the United States, Australia, the UK, and India, StarRez blends the robust capabilities of a global organization with the personalized care and service of a trusted partner.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 117, 219);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a talented, passionate, smart, resourceful, highly motivated sales professional to support our momentum and expansion in the EMEA student accommodation &amp;amp; PBSA market. If you love sales and have a passion for the student property management market — from new lead generation to closure — we want to connect with you! We are searching for talented tech-loving team players who want to positively impact millions of residents&#39; lives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will be responsible for achieving new business revenue goals within assigned territory. From initial lead generation through product demonstration, relationship development, closure, and ongoing account management, you will have complete ownership of the planning and execution of new business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 117, 219);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Specifics&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work Location: Remote (UK)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel: 25% (The percentage of travel is an estimation and could vary based on business needs.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reporting Structure: Reports to the Director of Sales, New Business.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 117, 219);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Own&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage assigned EMEA territory to achieve new customer acquisitions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Account management of new customer acquisitions until they’ve completed implementation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and manage tendering, RFP, and formal bid processes, including coordination with internal stakeholders to deliver competitive submissions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Outbound prospecting and market coverage via email, phone, social, and other mediums as required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and develop prospect and existing account pipeline from initial lead to deal closure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide market insight and customer requirements to better position existing solutions both online and in person&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide feedback for new product development and future evolution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build long-term relationships with prospects, customers, and industry leaders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage infrastructure tools such as Salesforce, Gong, ChatGPT, &amp;amp; Zoom, as well as collaboration tools such as Slack &amp;amp; SharePoint, and social tools such as LinkedIn Sales Navigator, to build market/prospect data for effective data analytics and market insight&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in creating and updating sales and marketing materials for web, print, and demonstration purposes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and develop effective partner relationships as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other duties as assigned&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 117, 219);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years in

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong data-stringify-type=&quot;bold&quot;&gt;About StarRez&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;StarRez is the global leader in student housing software, providing innovative solutions for on and off-campus housing management, resident wellness and experience, and revenue generation. Trusted by 1,400+ clients across 25+ countries, StarRez supports more than 4 million beds annually with its user-friendly, all-in-one platform, delivering seamless experiences for students and administrators. With offices in the United States, Australia, the UK, and India, StarRez blends the robust capabilities of a global organization with the personalized care and service of a trusted partner.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;StarRez is seeking an Account Manager to serve as a trusted partner to our community of EMEA customers.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;You will work closely with universities, PBSA operators, and student accommodation providers to understand their operational and strategic priorities, and position tailored StarRez solutions that deliver measurable value.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your mission is twofold: work alongside our internal teams to ensure customer happiness and success and drive growth by&amp;nbsp;identifying&amp;nbsp;upsell opportunities aligned to their needs. This role owns the full cycle of account growth from lead generation and product demonstration to&amp;nbsp;deal&amp;nbsp;closure with a strong emphasis on relationship-building, consultative selling, and customer success.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll&amp;nbsp;collaborate closely with colleagues across&amp;nbsp;Customer Success,&amp;nbsp;Product, Professional Services,&amp;nbsp;Renewals,&amp;nbsp;and Marketing, bringing insights from the field to influence strategy and outcomes. This is an excellent opportunity for a sales-oriented problem solver who thrives on making a measurable impact and building long-term partnerships&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will own the full sales cycle within existing accounts, from&amp;nbsp;identifying&amp;nbsp;expansion opportunities and conducting in-depth needs analysis to leading product demonstrations, managing tender processes, and closing deals. Success in this role requires the ability to&amp;nbsp;manage competing priorities, engage proactively with customers, and consistently deliver&amp;nbsp;against revenue, customer&amp;nbsp;engagement&amp;nbsp;and data integrity targets.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is ideal for a sales professional who thrives in a&amp;nbsp;metrics-driven environment, enjoys managing complex sales cycles, and is motivated by building long-term, commercially impactful partnerships.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Specifics&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work Location: Remote (UK)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel:&amp;nbsp;Up to&amp;nbsp;50%&amp;nbsp;(The percentage of travel is an estimation and may vary based on&amp;nbsp;business needs.)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reporting Structure: This role reports to the&amp;nbsp;Manager, Sales.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Own&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive revenue growth within an assigned EMEA territory and customer portfolio by&amp;nbsp;identifying&amp;nbsp;upsell and expansion opportunities, managing&amp;nbsp;pipeline, and consistently achieving or exceeding quota targets.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead complex, consultative sales cycles, including in-depth discovery, tailored product demonstrations, proposal development, negotiation, and deal closure&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and&amp;nbsp;maintain&amp;nbsp;trusted relationships with stakeholders across universities, PBSA&amp;nbsp;operators, and student

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong data-stringify-type=&quot;bold&quot;&gt;About StarRez&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;StarRez is the global leader in student housing software, providing innovative solutions for on and off-campus housing management, resident wellness and experience, and revenue generation. Trusted by 1,400+ clients across 25+ countries, StarRez supports more than 4 million beds annually with its user-friendly, all-in-one platform, delivering seamless experiences for students and administrators. With offices in the United States, Australia, the UK, and India, StarRez blends the robust capabilities of a global organization with the personalized care and service of a trusted partner.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(40, 114, 214);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;The Role&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;You have an uncanny knack for problem&amp;nbsp;solving&amp;nbsp;and you have a sharp product mindset. Our engineers are involved in all aspects of the software design process and create high-performing, scalable, and secure products.&amp;nbsp;You’ll&amp;nbsp;work alongside cross-functional teams to design right-size solutions that power a new market-leading Analytics platform.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;As a Data Engineer at&amp;nbsp;StarRez, you will play a critical role in building and scaling the foundations of our Analytics &amp;amp; Data Platform.&amp;nbsp;You’ll&amp;nbsp;design and&amp;nbsp;maintain&amp;nbsp;reliable, secure, and scalable data pipelines and models that power a new generation of reporting, insights, and data-driven products across the&amp;nbsp;StarRez&amp;nbsp;ecosystem.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;This role sits at the intersection of data, product, and engineering. You will work closely with Data Analysts, Full-Stack Engineers, and Product teams to translate customer and business requirements into robust data solutions&amp;nbsp;-&amp;nbsp;enabling everything from standardised dashboards to advanced analytics and embedded intelligence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;You are hands-on, pragmatic, and comfortable working in a fast-evolving environment where&amp;nbsp;you’ll&amp;nbsp;help shape both the technical platform and the operating model as we scale.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(40, 114, 214);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;What&amp;nbsp;you’ll&amp;nbsp;be doing&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-leveltext=&quot;&quot; data-font=&quot;Symbol&quot; data-listid=&quot;11&quot; data-list-defn-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;335552541&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:720,&amp;quot;335559991&amp;quot;:360,&amp;quot;469769226&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;Symbol&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469769242&amp;quot;:[8226],&amp;quot;469777803&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;left&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469777804&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469777815&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;multilevel&amp;quot;}&quot; data-aria-posinset=&quot;1&quot; data-aria-level=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Build and&amp;nbsp;maintain&amp;nbsp;scalable data pipelines to ingest, transform, and model data for analytics and reporting&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-leveltext=&quot;&quot; data-font=&quot

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong data-stringify-type=&quot;bold&quot;&gt;About StarRez&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;StarRez is the global leader in student housing software, providing innovative solutions for on and off-campus housing management, resident wellness and experience, and revenue generation. Trusted by 1,400+ clients across 25+ countries, StarRez supports more than 4 million beds annually with its user-friendly, all-in-one platform, delivering seamless experiences for students and administrators. With offices in the United States, Australia, the UK, and India, StarRez blends the robust capabilities of a global organization with the personalized care and service of a trusted partner.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 117, 219);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;The Role&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;As the Director, Sales, you will lead StarRez&#39;s North American Community Relations organization, driving long-term customer success, revenue growth, and strategic customer relationships across our existing customer base. You will lead a team of Sales Managers responsible for account management, customer engagement, and expansion opportunities while ensuring customers maximize the value of their partnership with StarRez.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;In addition to leading the North America Community Relations organization, this role serves as the strategic partner to Community Relations leadership across EMEA and APAC. While this position does not have direct management responsibility for those regional teams, it is accountable for driving global alignment across business processes, operational excellence, product and solution development, and revenue growth programs. The Director partners closely with regional leaders to share insights, standardize successful practices where appropriate, and deliver a consistent, world-class customer experience globally.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;In this role, you will establish the strategic direction for the Community Relations team, partnering closely with Sales, Professional Services, Product, Support, Marketing, and Executive Leadership to deliver an exceptional customer experience that drives retention, customer advocacy, and sustainable revenue growth. You are a collaborative, customer-focused leader who develops high-performing teams, builds trusted executive relationships, and leverages customer insights to influence business decisions.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 117, 219);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;Role Specifics&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Work Location:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt; Remote&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Travel:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt; Up to 40% (The percentage of travel is an estimation. It could vary based on business need.)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong data-stringify-type=&quot;bold&quot;&gt;About StarRez&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;StarRez is the global leader in student housing software, providing innovative solutions for on and off-campus housing management, resident wellness and experience, and revenue generation. Trusted by 1,400+ clients across 25+ countries, StarRez supports more than 4 million beds annually with its user-friendly, all-in-one platform, delivering seamless experiences for students and administrators. With offices in the United States, Australia, the UK, and India, StarRez blends the robust capabilities of a global organization with the personalized care and service of a trusted partner.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role &amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a People &amp;amp; Culture Business Partner at StarRez, you will be responsible for providing people and culture guidance and support to StarRez&#39;s team members, managers and executives. You will bring a comprehensive understanding of policies, practices, and processes to be a trusted partner to leadership. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will partner with the Senior Leadership team to ensure the successful delivery of all people and culture services, including but not limited to, workforce planning, performance management, performance reviews, surveys and reporting, recruitment and onboarding, management of people issues in consultation with and support from the P&amp;amp;C Vice President, Chief People Officer and department leaders. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Specifics &amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Work Location: Australia - Melbourne (Hybrid 3 days per week) &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Travel: &amp;lt;5% [The percent of travel is an estimation, and it could vary up or down based on business needs throughout the year.] &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting Structure: Reports to Vice President, People &amp;amp; Culture &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Application Deadline: &lt;/strong&gt;This role will accept applications until 3 July 2026, unless otherwise posted. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Own &amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as key partner, adviser and sounding board for leadership, providing council and collaboration across talent acquisition, organizational design, performance management, engagement, and growth and development  &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and execute talent strategy, policy and processes for People &amp;amp; Culture activities for StarRez team members in multiple geographies, including employment contracts, and employee handbooks in accordance with local labor laws. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with the P&amp;amp;C Vice President, Chief People Officer, and department leaders on people management activities including onboarding of new team members, performance management, learning and development, management of people issues and other activities as required &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foster a positive, inclusive and engaging workplace environment that aligns with company values, including leading, organizing and executing team member engagement initiatives, ensuring high morale and team collaboration &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the primary point of contact for people matters, resolving team member concerns and escalating issues as needed. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage Leave Administration, including Annual, Personal, Maternity/Paternity, etc. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
