&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;StarRez is the global leader in student housing software, providing innovative solutions for on and off-campus housing management, resident wellness and experience, and revenue generation. Trusted by 1,400+ clients across 25+ countries, StarRez supports more than 4 million beds annually with its user-friendly, all-in-one platform, delivering seamless experiences for students and administrators. With offices in the United States, Australia, the UK, and India, StarRez blends the robust capabilities of a global organization with the personalized care and service of a trusted partner.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #0075db; font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;The Role&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #0075db; font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You have an uncanny knack for problem solving and you have a sharp product mindset. Our Tech Leads are involved in all aspects of the software design process and create high-performing, scalable, and secure products. This is a hands-on technical role, with no people management responsibilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the most senior technical person in your team, you’ll be hands-on in the solution and code, working alongside Product, Design, Quality, Platform, Security and your team to design solutions that power a new market-leading Analytics platform. You aren’t afraid to challenge the status quo and define solutions that sit outside of existing patterns, especially where reliability, security, and repeatability are critical to customer success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role you will own the engineering foundations of StarRez’s Analytics &amp;amp; Reporting capabilities, leading the development of a new Analytics product and the implementation of a new cloud data warehouse. You will lead the build of the data model integration layer, including automated customer schema provisioning, user provisioning, and Single Sign-On (SSO) integration (SAML/OIDC) to deliver a seamless and secure customer experience. You will also uplift existing ad-hoc reporting and analytics tools, and assist with improving the StarRez database schema, working closely with Data Analysts, Engineers and Product Managers to align the platform to best practice and analytics readiness.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Inter, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;With deep knowledge of your domain and programming language, you not only understand how choices made in software design and architecture affect areas like performance, maintainability, testability, observability, and security, you teach and promote this knowledge to others within and across teams. You are hands-on and keep up to date with the latest .NET and web technologies.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
